The Incom T-65 X-wing starfighter is the main all-purpose starfighter of the Rebel Alliance and its sucessor governments. Known for its versatility and good combat performance, it is a favorite with Rebel and New Republic pilots. Possessing deflector shields, a hyperdrive, an R2 astromech for repairs and navigation, and a complement of proton torpedoes, the X-wing allows the Rebellion to launch raids in Imperial space with improved odds of a successful mission.

Pilots of Rogue Squadron favor using the multi-role X-wing fighter, flying it as often as they can on most missions; they only employ other crafts for highly specialized missions, such as missions that required ion cannons. The X-wing is so predominately flown by Rebel forces that it became a symbol of their faction, much like the TIE fighter and Star Destroyer are symbols of the Galactic Empire.
